WEBVTT

01:26.110 --> 01:34.990
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.470 --> 01:37.820
[Episode 12]

02:21.960 --> 02:24.500
Just because you have a few bucks,

02:25.130 --> 02:26.790
you're starting to get cocky?

02:28.090 --> 02:29.900
A big horse is worth money,

02:29.960 --> 02:31.360
but a person with a big ego

02:31.630 --> 02:32.930
is worthless.

02:33.300 --> 02:33.960
Get to work!

02:43.000 --> 02:43.930
"Is she pretty?"

02:45.690 --> 02:48.240
Dong'er lit a cigarette and asked.

02:49.120 --> 02:50.780
Wu Xiaoshuai answered...

02:53.800 --> 02:54.460
"Average."

02:55.150 --> 02:56.520
Dong'er blew out a puff of smoke.

02:56.520 --> 02:57.430
She smiled and said...

02:57.430 --> 02:57.970
They...

03:00.150 --> 03:01.210
"Don't be nervous.

03:02.130 --> 03:04.250
I'm not trying to seduce you."

03:05.360 --> 03:06.450
What are you doing?

03:07.020 --> 03:07.680
What are you doing?

03:07.680 --> 03:09.010
I... Master, I am trying

03:09.180 --> 03:10.410
to get into the character's head.

03:10.410 --> 03:11.030
Look at us.

03:11.030 --> 03:11.690
With this back and forth dialogue,

03:11.690 --> 03:12.400
the romantic tension

03:12.400 --> 03:13.930
just builds up, doesn't it?

03:14.000 --> 03:15.060
Who is your master?

03:15.520 --> 03:16.930
Who is getting romantic with you?

03:16.930 --> 03:17.910
You are ruining

03:17.910 --> 03:19.190
the atmosphere like this.

03:19.190 --> 03:20.020
I was thinking

03:20.430 --> 03:21.240
that this is the first time

03:21.240 --> 03:21.900
the two of them are sharing

03:21.900 --> 03:22.960
a confined space.

03:23.090 --> 03:23.400
Right.

03:23.400 --> 03:24.500
If you keep chatting like this,

03:24.500 --> 03:25.710
it... it will be hard to end well.

03:25.710 --> 03:26.500
Well, look.

03:26.870 --> 03:27.470
Dong'er

03:27.620 --> 03:29.400
has a lot of pride.

03:29.579 --> 03:31.500
She would never hand the initiative

03:31.500 --> 03:32.860
over to Wu Xiaoshuai.

03:33.250 --> 03:34.780
Sometimes, to break

03:34.780 --> 03:35.960
the ambiguous atmosphere,

03:35.960 --> 03:37.250
the best way is to

03:37.970 --> 03:39.030
make things clear.

03:40.310 --> 03:41.020
I think

03:41.300 --> 03:42.430
that you forgot our rules

03:42.430 --> 03:43.810
in the blink of an eye.

03:44.460 --> 03:45.460
Put your hand out.

03:45.520 --> 03:46.180
Hand out!

03:46.430 --> 03:47.650
Hurry, hand out!

03:52.360 --> 03:54.370
Forget it, forget it.

03:57.300 --> 03:59.120
Water. Water. Give me some water.

03:59.120 --> 03:59.579
Water.

04:00.500 --> 04:01.640
Slow down. Slow down.

04:01.640 --> 04:02.250
Slowly.

04:02.590 --> 04:03.060
Good.

04:04.780 --> 04:06.780
Did you learn your lesson this time?

04:07.690 --> 04:09.020
Sit down. Keep writing.

04:09.590 --> 04:10.390
Keep writing.

04:14.750 --> 04:22.460
[Registration Room]

04:15.430 --> 04:17.800
You want me to open the door at this hour?

04:17.800 --> 04:18.600
I'm really sorry.

04:18.600 --> 04:19.920
The rooster hasn't even crowed yet.

04:19.920 --> 04:20.250
Yeah.

04:20.660 --> 04:21.930
What kind of job is this?

04:21.930 --> 04:23.060
Sorry to bother you.

04:23.270 --> 04:24.530
It's a bothersome job.

04:26.740 --> 04:27.830
Here, bro.

04:27.980 --> 04:28.890
Take this.

04:29.560 --> 04:30.360
I'm always troubling you.

04:30.360 --> 04:31.690
Take it and have a smoke.

04:32.330 --> 04:32.870
No need.

04:32.950 --> 04:34.150
I'm just doing my job.

04:35.159 --> 04:36.190
If you need anything, just say the word.

04:36.190 --> 04:37.060
What do you mean "just doing your job"?

04:37.060 --> 04:37.920
I can't always be bothering you.

04:37.920 --> 04:38.310
Morning.

04:38.310 --> 04:39.770
Another night owl is back.

04:41.510 --> 04:42.750
Roommate, roommate!

04:48.180 --> 04:49.810
You're up even earlier than me.

04:49.810 --> 04:51.300
Where are you coming back from?

04:51.300 --> 04:52.310
Writing scripts

04:52.330 --> 04:53.530
has no schedule to it.

04:54.570 --> 04:55.570
Writing scripts?

04:56.250 --> 04:57.620
So you're an artist?

04:57.890 --> 04:59.090
Something like that.

04:59.120 --> 05:00.330
Must be making a ton of money, right?

05:00.330 --> 05:01.450
I don't make money.

05:01.450 --> 05:02.810
I'm studying with a mentor.

05:02.810 --> 05:03.540
Look at you.

05:03.860 --> 05:05.460
You really don't make money?

05:06.690 --> 05:07.480
If you don't make money,

05:07.480 --> 05:09.280
why are you so happy all the time?

05:09.360 --> 05:11.270
I thought you were making a fortune.

05:11.270 --> 05:12.750
I don't get your industry.

05:13.360 --> 05:14.720
I thought you artists

05:14.720 --> 05:15.360
just messed around

05:15.360 --> 05:16.230
and the money rolled in.

05:16.230 --> 05:16.810
No, no.

05:16.950 --> 05:18.300
No one has it easy, right?

05:18.300 --> 05:19.890
But you're up early
and back late every day.

05:19.890 --> 05:20.690
What do you do?

05:23.120 --> 05:23.980
Let me tell you.

05:24.070 --> 05:26.200
My company sent me here to Beijing.

05:26.680 --> 05:27.250
The dorm

05:27.250 --> 05:28.360
isn't ready for me yet.

05:28.360 --> 05:29.720
Otherwise, I wouldn't be staying here.

05:29.720 --> 05:32.050
The work started before my dorm was ready.

05:32.270 --> 05:33.040
They want me to buy

05:33.040 --> 05:35.100
train tickets for the whole company.

05:35.980 --> 05:36.830
Let me tell you.

05:36.830 --> 05:38.720
Just to earn this little subsidy,

05:39.010 --> 05:39.720
I have to get up this early

05:39.720 --> 05:41.010
and queue up to buy tickets for people.

05:41.010 --> 05:42.010
That's not easy either.

05:42.010 --> 05:43.810
But at least you make some money.

05:45.750 --> 05:47.150
Let me ask you something.

05:47.270 --> 05:48.930
Is this always your schedule?

05:49.810 --> 05:51.610
My schedule isn't that regular.

05:52.740 --> 05:54.270
I don't mean anything else.

05:54.430 --> 05:55.800
We can cooperate.

05:56.560 --> 05:58.159
You can make some extra cash.

05:58.770 --> 05:59.970
Let me put it this way.

06:00.370 --> 06:01.540
Getting up early for me

06:01.540 --> 06:02.920
is a huge struggle.

06:03.500 --> 06:05.420
Since you're up at this time anyway,

06:05.420 --> 06:07.000
you can just go to the station

06:07.000 --> 06:08.330
and grab tickets for me.

06:08.500 --> 06:09.540
I won't let you do it for free.

06:09.540 --> 06:10.980
I'll give you 50 a trip.

06:11.480 --> 06:11.980
Deal?

06:12.930 --> 06:14.060
Fifty a trip?

06:17.870 --> 06:19.000
But my teacher

06:19.040 --> 06:20.040
sleeps on and off.

06:20.060 --> 06:21.740
His schedule is very irregular.

06:21.740 --> 06:23.490
I'm afraid I'll hold you up.

06:24.680 --> 06:26.610
I thought you found the pay too low.

06:26.860 --> 06:27.770
I understand.

06:28.190 --> 06:29.050
How about this.

06:29.120 --> 06:30.950
When you get a regular schedule,

06:31.390 --> 06:32.120
let me know.

06:32.690 --> 06:34.640
I'll save this job for you.

06:34.740 --> 06:35.200
Okay?

06:36.060 --> 06:36.430
Okay.

06:37.190 --> 06:37.740
I'm off.

06:39.130 --> 06:39.830
Thanks.

06:40.000 --> 06:40.860
Don't mention it.

06:40.860 --> 06:42.860
We're roommates. Don't mention it.

06:44.770 --> 06:46.970
With this temporary residence permit,

06:47.390 --> 06:48.950
we count as Beijingers now.

06:49.810 --> 06:51.310
At most, we're...

06:51.430 --> 06:53.330
temporary Beijingers.

06:54.300 --> 06:55.960
Don't you know how to round up?

06:56.060 --> 06:57.540
You can round this up?

06:57.570 --> 06:58.220
Why not?

06:58.870 --> 06:59.800
Let me see yours.

07:04.250 --> 07:05.510
You look quite proper.

07:06.540 --> 07:08.030
But it didn't capture your charm.

07:08.030 --> 07:12.560
[Name: Xu Shengli]

07:08.310 --> 07:09.830
What charm?

07:14.060 --> 07:15.190
An adorkable charm.

07:15.310 --> 07:17.560
[Name: Xu Shengli]

07:17.860 --> 07:19.240
Who's a dork?

07:31.570 --> 07:31.920
By the way,

07:31.920 --> 07:33.450
how are your classes going?

07:35.860 --> 07:36.690
My teacher

07:37.720 --> 07:38.830
has a weird temper.

07:39.920 --> 07:41.320
He's a bit hard to please.

07:42.000 --> 07:43.420
Maybe you didn't do something right.

07:43.420 --> 07:45.040
What didn't I do right?

07:45.930 --> 07:46.740
Every day,

07:47.600 --> 07:48.630
he talks and I write,

07:48.630 --> 07:49.630
I cook and he eats,

07:49.870 --> 07:50.950
I read and he scolds me.

07:50.950 --> 07:52.130
I've been diligent,

07:52.130 --> 07:53.540
steady, and meticulous.

07:55.130 --> 07:56.190
You can cook?

07:59.270 --> 08:00.530
Wait, what do you mean?

08:01.330 --> 08:02.500
You're mocking me.

08:02.770 --> 08:04.120
I may not be good at it,

08:04.120 --> 08:05.250
but I can still do it.

08:05.770 --> 08:06.890
With your skills?

08:07.750 --> 08:08.420
My skills

08:08.450 --> 08:09.720
were learned from you.

08:09.750 --> 08:11.040
I definitely cook better than you.

08:11.040 --> 08:11.560
Fine.

08:11.740 --> 08:12.600
You're better.

08:15.190 --> 08:15.950
Could it be that the problem

08:15.950 --> 08:17.080
lies in the food?

08:17.560 --> 08:18.180
If people don't eat well,

08:18.180 --> 08:19.710
they tend to get irritable.

08:21.060 --> 08:22.790
I've heard of morning temper,

08:23.220 --> 08:24.810
but I've never heard of food temper.

08:24.810 --> 08:25.360
He's just eating.

08:25.360 --> 08:26.740
How can he get so worked up?

08:26.740 --> 08:28.360
Well, that's the extent of my skills.

08:28.360 --> 08:29.360
I can't help it.

08:29.500 --> 08:30.260
Learn.

08:30.450 --> 08:31.120
Learn?

08:31.180 --> 08:32.510
Who should I learn from?

08:35.549 --> 08:37.679
Wipe yourself. You got it all over you.

08:39.250 --> 08:40.780
Where is your teacher from?

08:40.909 --> 08:41.700
Sichuan.

08:52.500 --> 08:53.910
Don't you understand the principle

08:53.910 --> 08:55.510
of catering to one's tastes?

08:55.700 --> 08:56.700
Sichuan cuisine?

08:57.530 --> 08:58.150
Sure.

08:58.530 --> 08:59.930
Then I'll learn from you.

09:00.130 --> 09:01.240
I'm from Wenzhou

09:01.250 --> 09:03.000
and you want to learn
Sichuan cuisine from me?

09:03.000 --> 09:04.170
Then I'll learn Wenzhou cuisine

09:04.170 --> 09:04.750
from you

09:04.770 --> 09:06.670
and I'll add some chili peppers.
Won't that work?

09:06.670 --> 09:07.210
Fine.

09:07.460 --> 09:07.790
Okay.

09:11.130 --> 09:11.460
Okay.

09:11.460 --> 09:12.750
I'll ask around for you later

09:12.750 --> 09:14.570
to see who can cook Sichuan cuisine.

09:14.570 --> 09:14.940
Okay.

09:15.750 --> 09:16.680
You're the best.

09:17.530 --> 09:18.330
Really great.

09:19.700 --> 09:20.500
How about you?

09:20.550 --> 09:22.150
How's your troupe audition?

09:26.770 --> 09:27.720
Something happened?

09:27.720 --> 09:29.220
Tell me, what went wrong?

09:29.270 --> 09:30.170
Don't ask.

09:30.620 --> 09:32.350
Mr. Zheng paid my tuition fees.

09:32.430 --> 09:33.790
I saved up some money to pay him back,

09:33.790 --> 09:34.510
but Mrs. Zheng

09:34.510 --> 09:35.820
caught us right in the act.

09:35.820 --> 09:36.700
Now look what happened.

09:36.700 --> 09:38.560
Mr. Zheng got dragged into it too.

09:43.960 --> 09:44.960
If you ask me,

09:45.650 --> 09:46.650
it's not that bad.

09:48.150 --> 09:49.410
I still feel terrible.

09:50.320 --> 09:52.050
It puts Mr. Zheng in a tough spot.

09:52.050 --> 09:53.580
If you feel shy,

09:53.580 --> 09:54.580
then don't go.

09:56.770 --> 09:59.100
Don't make me kick you into the lake!

09:59.890 --> 10:00.250
Fine.

10:00.960 --> 10:02.890
I'll figure something out for you.

10:05.250 --> 10:06.980
Let me ask you three questions.

10:07.150 --> 10:07.910
First,

10:07.960 --> 10:09.910
is Mr. Zheng the person

10:10.270 --> 10:11.460
that Mrs. Zheng cares most about?

10:11.460 --> 10:12.060
Of course.

10:12.250 --> 10:12.710
Second,

10:13.080 --> 10:14.390
do you and Mrs. Zheng

10:14.440 --> 10:15.100
talk often?

10:16.370 --> 10:17.030
Not really.

10:17.120 --> 10:17.630
Third,

10:18.130 --> 10:19.760
does Mr. Zheng usually

10:20.030 --> 10:21.340
take good care of you?

10:23.620 --> 10:25.220
That's exactly the problem.

10:25.650 --> 10:26.380
Listen to me.

10:27.870 --> 10:29.480
The next time you go,

10:29.740 --> 10:30.860
dress a bit more plainly.

10:30.860 --> 10:32.220
Don't look too flashy.

10:32.670 --> 10:34.530
I look flashy?

10:35.150 --> 10:35.550
Me?

10:35.580 --> 10:35.940
No.

10:36.650 --> 10:37.080
No, no, no.

10:37.080 --> 10:37.680
No, no, no.

10:37.790 --> 10:39.340
That's not what I mean.

10:39.720 --> 10:40.820
What I mean is...

10:42.720 --> 10:44.460
You're already

10:44.510 --> 10:45.440
very pretty.

10:45.960 --> 10:46.500
You...

10:46.500 --> 10:48.290
So if you dress up even a little,

10:48.620 --> 10:49.360
you just look really,

10:49.360 --> 10:50.420
really beautiful.

10:50.650 --> 10:51.790
It's human nature

10:51.840 --> 10:52.770
to be jealous.

10:53.290 --> 10:54.530
Especially since Mrs. Zheng

10:54.530 --> 10:56.190
cares so much about Mr. Zheng.

10:56.250 --> 10:56.700
Go on.

10:57.250 --> 10:58.120
Anyway,

10:59.240 --> 11:01.130
you need to get closer

11:01.750 --> 11:02.770
to Mrs. Zheng.

11:03.770 --> 11:05.510
Even if you want to talk to Mr. Zheng,

11:05.510 --> 11:06.480
you have to go through

11:06.480 --> 11:07.480
Mrs. Zheng first.

11:09.150 --> 11:10.030
For a grown man,

11:10.030 --> 11:11.760
you sure know a lot about women.

11:12.550 --> 11:14.210
You flirted with a lot of girls

11:14.650 --> 11:16.650
in your salted fish factory, right?

11:16.980 --> 11:18.440
I didn't have to do that.

11:18.460 --> 11:20.790
They all talked to me first.

11:27.410 --> 11:28.510
Anyway, from now on,

11:28.510 --> 11:29.650
if anything happens,

11:29.650 --> 11:30.380
just tell me.

11:32.000 --> 11:33.660
We'll figure it out together.

11:34.240 --> 11:35.370
You said it before.

11:36.250 --> 11:38.120
Don't shoulder it all by yourself.

11:38.120 --> 11:40.240
It's no big deal. I can handle it.

11:43.030 --> 11:43.630
By the way,

11:44.100 --> 11:44.980
that Gut Cook

11:45.010 --> 11:47.170
hasn't been bothering you lately, has he?

11:47.170 --> 11:47.830
Let him try.

11:48.220 --> 11:50.350
I've still got plenty of pepper spray.

11:51.170 --> 11:51.580
Good.

11:52.130 --> 11:53.530
I have more if you run out.

11:58.150 --> 11:59.820
When I first came to Beijing,

12:00.170 --> 12:01.770
I thought this city was huge.

12:02.860 --> 12:04.120
Just getting to class takes

12:04.120 --> 12:05.460
an hour and a half by bus.

12:06.170 --> 12:07.180
A round trip

12:08.030 --> 12:10.160
is enough to circle my hometown twice.

12:12.910 --> 12:13.750
But after Kang Shunyin

12:13.750 --> 12:14.750
made such a scene,

12:16.620 --> 12:18.080
I have a new understanding

12:20.120 --> 12:21.450
of Beijing's vastness.

12:23.820 --> 12:24.670
Here,

12:25.790 --> 12:27.670
no one cares about your madness

12:29.010 --> 12:30.410
or your joys and sorrows.

12:32.320 --> 12:33.220
Maybe that is

12:33.240 --> 12:34.840
a special kind of tolerance.

12:36.080 --> 12:36.680
It's nice.

12:37.940 --> 12:38.740
It feels free.

12:40.440 --> 12:40.860
Yeah.

12:42.700 --> 12:43.390
In Beijing,

12:44.740 --> 12:46.600
no matter how successful you are,

12:47.530 --> 12:48.370
this big city

12:49.290 --> 12:49.980
won't think

12:50.000 --> 12:51.000
you're a big deal.

12:52.700 --> 12:54.290
If you just want to lie around,

12:54.290 --> 12:54.940
Beijing

12:55.410 --> 12:56.870
won't kick you out either.

12:57.500 --> 12:59.030
No one cares about you here!

13:01.100 --> 13:02.360
But everyone asks,

13:04.000 --> 13:05.000
"Have you eaten?"

13:09.740 --> 13:11.360
Whether you're a big shot

13:12.440 --> 13:13.410
or a nobody,

13:15.860 --> 13:17.860
don't take yourself too seriously.

13:17.910 --> 13:20.370
But you can't think
you're nothing, either.

13:26.940 --> 13:27.340
Right.

13:31.600 --> 13:33.890
Will you stay in Beijing forever?

13:36.410 --> 13:37.080
I hope so.

13:38.550 --> 13:39.840
I hope I can too!

13:42.600 --> 13:44.730
When our temporary residence permits

13:44.750 --> 13:45.740
gets renewed,

13:46.150 --> 13:47.680
we'll go get them together!

14:06.670 --> 14:07.200
Zongbao,

14:08.050 --> 14:09.100
I originally wanted

14:09.100 --> 14:10.320
to come back for a nap.

14:11.120 --> 14:12.240
I realized that Li Xiaobo

14:12.240 --> 14:13.170
is acting really shady.

14:13.170 --> 14:15.340
He was secretly handing someone money.

14:15.340 --> 14:16.720
He gets up at the crack of dawn too.

14:16.720 --> 14:17.860
He doesn't look like someone

14:17.860 --> 14:19.080
who does honest work.

14:19.250 --> 14:20.180
What do you mean?

14:20.550 --> 14:21.980
Are you saying

14:22.320 --> 14:23.390
he's not a good person?

14:23.390 --> 14:23.820
I...

14:24.840 --> 14:26.150
I met him this morning.

14:26.620 --> 14:27.620
He said he went to

14:27.630 --> 14:28.790
buy train tickets.

14:29.600 --> 14:29.980
What?

14:31.200 --> 14:32.000
He's a ticket scalper?

14:32.000 --> 14:32.600
No, no, no.

14:32.890 --> 14:33.600
He said it's for...

14:33.600 --> 14:35.600
He said he's buying for his company.

14:39.080 --> 14:40.980
Alright. Let's keep an eye on him.

14:41.600 --> 14:43.250
He's just not a good person.

14:45.530 --> 14:46.060
Zongbao.

14:46.650 --> 14:48.240
Add some more chili peppers.

14:48.240 --> 14:48.750
More?

14:50.010 --> 14:50.370
Sure.

14:50.980 --> 14:52.050
No matter how many peppers you add,

14:52.050 --> 14:53.700
it's all just veggies.

14:53.770 --> 14:55.030
Zongbao, make some meat dishes,

14:55.030 --> 14:55.620
alright?

14:55.650 --> 14:56.740
These past few days, I...

14:56.740 --> 14:57.630
Where are we gonna get meat?

14:57.630 --> 14:58.510
Are you paying?

14:58.600 --> 15:00.100
Let's all chip in.

15:00.630 --> 15:02.120
My pants are about to fall off.

15:02.120 --> 15:03.130
I want meat too.

15:03.170 --> 15:04.130
You're all here?

15:04.410 --> 15:04.770
You're back?

15:04.770 --> 15:05.530
Chatting?

15:05.740 --> 15:06.340
Let me see.

15:06.670 --> 15:08.270
What good food are you making?

15:08.270 --> 15:09.460
Stir-frying two veggie dishes.

15:09.460 --> 15:10.590
Let's eat together.

15:11.740 --> 15:12.740
That's too plain.

15:13.100 --> 15:13.740
For us men,

15:13.740 --> 15:14.980
we can't treat our stomachs poorly.

15:14.980 --> 15:16.380
We need some meat dishes.

15:16.410 --> 15:16.790
Just in time.

15:16.790 --> 15:18.320
I'll add a meat dish for you.

15:18.360 --> 15:18.790
Look.

15:19.530 --> 15:20.550
Roast chicken.

15:22.410 --> 15:23.360
Sorry about today.

15:23.360 --> 15:24.080
It's fine.

15:24.550 --> 15:24.980
Here.

15:25.480 --> 15:27.010
Also got a bottle of liquor.

15:27.500 --> 15:28.550
I got up too early.

15:28.600 --> 15:29.670
I've been looking for a chance

15:29.670 --> 15:31.410
to treat you guys to some food and drink.

15:31.410 --> 15:32.430
Eat the roast chicken while it's hot.

15:32.430 --> 15:33.410
It goes well with your veggie dishes.

15:33.410 --> 15:33.810
Great.

15:33.980 --> 15:34.620
Great.

15:34.630 --> 15:35.650
You're too kind.

15:35.720 --> 15:36.890
No, no. Don't mention it. Come on.

15:36.890 --> 15:37.550
I'll leave this here for you.

15:37.550 --> 15:39.010
We usually drink this too.

15:39.670 --> 15:40.630
I put it on the table for you.

15:40.630 --> 15:41.830
There's more liquor.

15:41.980 --> 15:42.720
Dig in.

15:42.860 --> 15:43.790
-You're too kind.
-Hurry up.

15:43.790 --> 15:44.550
Look at him.

15:45.100 --> 15:45.920
So generous.

15:46.220 --> 15:48.010
You just follow whoever feeds you.

15:48.010 --> 15:49.070
Then don't eat any.

15:49.410 --> 15:49.910
Stir it.

15:53.050 --> 15:54.250
Why are you in bed?

15:54.290 --> 15:55.380
Come eat with us.

15:55.480 --> 15:55.880
No, no.

15:56.320 --> 15:57.200
I already ate.

15:57.290 --> 15:59.220
I won't stand on ceremony with you.

15:59.440 --> 16:00.200
Join us.

16:00.240 --> 16:00.630
Eat.

16:00.630 --> 16:02.120
I get up too early every day.
I'm sleep-deprived.

16:02.120 --> 16:02.770
I'm going to sleep.

16:02.770 --> 16:03.500
You guys eat.

16:03.550 --> 16:04.440
Go to sleep.

16:05.150 --> 16:06.740
Pull the blanket up.

16:07.500 --> 16:08.700
Cover your stomach.

16:08.740 --> 16:10.270
It's damp in this basement.

16:11.200 --> 16:12.480
You sleep. Sleep.

16:12.620 --> 16:13.350
Thanks, bro.

16:13.500 --> 16:14.430
You're welcome.

16:18.130 --> 16:19.150
Well, this...

16:19.440 --> 16:19.960
I'll...

16:20.650 --> 16:21.980
mix some dipping sauce.

16:22.170 --> 16:23.550
And shred the chicken.

16:24.150 --> 16:24.480
Okay.

16:30.480 --> 16:31.010
Zongbao.

16:31.270 --> 16:31.720
What?

16:32.820 --> 16:33.510
I think

16:33.740 --> 16:35.410
he just wants to use roast chicken

16:35.410 --> 16:36.140
to shut us up.

16:38.170 --> 16:39.320
I'll mix some more sauce

16:39.320 --> 16:40.370
to open

16:40.390 --> 16:41.480
your mouth.

16:41.750 --> 16:44.150
Whether my mouth's open or shut,

16:44.700 --> 16:45.500
it won't stop

16:45.500 --> 16:46.630
my suspicion of him.

16:47.270 --> 16:48.720
What are you suspicious of?

16:48.720 --> 16:50.500
Always suspicious of this and that.

16:50.500 --> 16:51.500
You suspect anyone

16:51.500 --> 16:52.910
that walks into Room 108,

16:53.320 --> 16:54.130
just like how

16:54.460 --> 16:56.410
you treated Xu Shengli back then.

16:56.730 --> 16:57.670
No, about Shengli...

16:57.670 --> 16:58.200
Shengli!

16:58.410 --> 17:00.210
Where are you going? Not eating?

17:00.910 --> 17:01.440
Shengli.

17:02.860 --> 17:03.320
This...

17:07.680 --> 17:08.480
MSG.

17:16.790 --> 17:17.960
I'm not eating either, Zongbao.

17:17.960 --> 17:19.069
What? Why aren't you eating?

17:19.069 --> 17:20.660
I just finished mixing the sauce.

17:20.660 --> 17:22.660
Even roast chicken can't shut me up.

17:26.220 --> 17:26.619
Great.

17:29.850 --> 17:30.780
Not eating, huh?

17:33.680 --> 17:35.680
I'll eat the chicken myself.

17:40.510 --> 17:40.970
This...

17:41.920 --> 17:43.380
This isn't roast chicken.

17:43.960 --> 17:45.980
It's a specimen.

17:49.330 --> 17:50.010
It's okay.

17:50.350 --> 17:51.950
If not, I can just borrow one.

17:54.000 --> 17:54.680
No rush.

17:56.530 --> 17:57.730
You're the best, Mom.

18:01.140 --> 18:02.000
I'm hanging up.

18:15.200 --> 18:16.060
Hello, Yan.

18:16.310 --> 18:17.680
I have a favor to ask you.

18:18.830 --> 18:19.740
Do you have

18:19.740 --> 18:21.070
a spare sewing machine?

18:23.110 --> 18:24.270
Could I borrow it for a few days?

18:24.270 --> 18:25.220
I want to alter

18:25.270 --> 18:26.400
some clothes later.

18:27.920 --> 18:28.650
Thanks, Yan.

18:29.420 --> 18:29.750
Okay.

18:34.500 --> 18:34.900
Done.

18:39.090 --> 18:40.820
You didn't go to Mr. He's place?

18:42.050 --> 18:43.480
I haven't finished the task

18:43.480 --> 18:44.660
he assigned me.

18:44.810 --> 18:46.670
Then why don't you hurry up and go?

18:47.380 --> 18:49.140
Five minutes won't make a difference.

18:49.140 --> 18:49.900
Look who's talking.

18:49.900 --> 18:50.610
It's Friday.

18:50.610 --> 18:52.070
Didn't you skip class too?

18:52.510 --> 18:53.030
Me?

18:53.680 --> 18:55.310
I wanted to practice on my own
at home today.

18:55.310 --> 18:56.370
Is there a problem?

18:56.790 --> 18:58.220
Practicing at home alone

18:58.250 --> 19:01.000
isn't as good as practicing
at the teacher's home.

19:01.000 --> 19:02.030
When it comes to singing,

19:02.030 --> 19:03.400
you think you know more than I do?

19:03.400 --> 19:04.770
Are you not going

19:04.790 --> 19:05.880
because of the money?

19:05.880 --> 19:06.680
Of course not.

19:08.680 --> 19:09.400
Don't worry

19:10.740 --> 19:11.670
about the money.

19:12.500 --> 19:13.700
What? I don't want it.

19:14.700 --> 19:15.830
Just open it and see.

19:16.200 --> 19:16.960
No.

19:18.010 --> 19:18.830
Open it.

19:29.240 --> 19:30.070
A drumstick?

19:30.850 --> 19:31.460
Where did you get this?

19:31.460 --> 19:32.290
Don't worry about that.

19:32.290 --> 19:34.690
Do you know more about chicken legs
than me?

19:39.420 --> 19:40.820
Why aren't you eating it?

19:41.090 --> 19:42.690
I'll enjoy it when I get back.

19:46.660 --> 19:47.320
Did you eat?

19:47.380 --> 19:47.740
I did.

19:48.070 --> 19:49.740
I ate the other drumstick.

19:51.920 --> 19:52.480
Thanks.

19:52.530 --> 19:53.460
You're welcome.

19:58.140 --> 19:58.920
The noodles are ready.

19:58.920 --> 19:59.580
Come and eat

19:59.740 --> 20:00.830
before it gets clumpy.

20:00.830 --> 20:01.400
Coming.

20:03.200 --> 20:04.110
Smells good.

20:04.110 --> 20:04.530
Look.

20:08.550 --> 20:09.740
A drumstick?

20:17.270 --> 20:18.810
I have one too.

20:21.270 --> 20:22.960
You eat yours, I'll eat mine.

20:23.030 --> 20:24.000
We'll each eat our own.

20:24.000 --> 20:24.480
Okay.

20:25.290 --> 20:26.310
One for each of us.

20:28.180 --> 20:29.180
It smells so good.

20:30.180 --> 20:32.040
Be careful, it's hot. Eat slowly.

20:33.810 --> 20:34.670
Is it too bland?

20:34.850 --> 20:35.570
It's just right.

20:35.570 --> 20:37.290
Your throat can't handle
salty food anyway.

20:37.290 --> 20:38.150
So thoughtful.

20:39.420 --> 20:40.020
By the way,

20:40.680 --> 20:42.460
You practice singing every day.

20:42.460 --> 20:43.920
Can your throat take it?

20:44.180 --> 20:44.780
It's okay.

20:47.920 --> 20:48.550
But usually,

20:48.550 --> 20:50.350
I do need to take care of my voice.

20:51.270 --> 20:52.670
Liangliang told me today

20:53.010 --> 20:55.140
that their bar is looking for a singer.

20:55.270 --> 20:56.440
Do you want to give it a try?

20:56.440 --> 20:58.440
You can practice and make money too.

20:59.440 --> 21:01.770
They're hiring pop singers,
aren't they?

21:04.220 --> 21:06.020
Singing folk songs and pop songs

21:06.160 --> 21:07.360
are quite different.

21:08.090 --> 21:09.200
If I sing too much pop,

21:09.200 --> 21:09.850
my vocal placement

21:09.850 --> 21:11.050
could easily change.

21:11.400 --> 21:12.800
What if you switch to pop?

21:13.010 --> 21:13.440
Look,

21:13.590 --> 21:14.500
so many stars

21:14.500 --> 21:15.530
sing pop.

21:16.050 --> 21:17.650
They get both money and fame.

21:23.700 --> 21:24.960
But singing folk songs

21:25.420 --> 21:26.240
and joining the troupe

21:26.240 --> 21:27.570
is why I came to Beijing.

21:28.830 --> 21:30.490
I can't give up just for money.

21:30.900 --> 21:32.470
What will you do if you can't

21:32.510 --> 21:33.640
get into the troupe?

21:34.900 --> 21:36.070
Then what if no one

21:36.090 --> 21:37.020
hires you to act?

21:37.550 --> 21:38.770
Then I'll keep going until the end.

21:38.770 --> 21:39.460
I don't believe

21:39.460 --> 21:40.610
no one will ever hire me.

21:40.610 --> 21:41.420
Me too.

21:47.380 --> 21:48.440
Eat the drumstick.

21:52.050 --> 21:52.510
Come on.

21:52.790 --> 21:54.190
Cheers with drumsticks.

21:56.850 --> 21:58.330
-It's so good.
-So good.

22:10.510 --> 22:12.640
Have a drumstick to cool off.

22:14.880 --> 22:16.010
Never heard of that.

22:16.270 --> 22:17.750
A friend of mine said,

22:18.350 --> 22:20.410
"Eating well keeps the temper down."

22:20.770 --> 22:21.570
I bought these erjingtiao peppers

22:21.570 --> 22:22.700
early this morning.

22:22.720 --> 22:25.250
I didn't dare overcook them
for even a second.

22:25.750 --> 22:26.480
Who did you

22:27.640 --> 22:29.010
learn this from?

22:29.240 --> 22:29.900
A friend...

22:30.720 --> 22:31.380
of a friend.

22:32.740 --> 22:33.770
I mean,

22:34.740 --> 22:35.670
who did you learn

22:36.310 --> 22:38.220
your sweet-talking tricks

22:38.570 --> 22:39.750
from?

22:40.010 --> 22:41.480
Then I'll tell you the truth.

22:41.480 --> 22:42.420
I learned it from

22:42.940 --> 22:44.870
"The Legend of the Condor Heroes."

22:47.420 --> 22:49.350
You're treating me as Hong Qigong?

22:49.480 --> 22:50.660
You cook a meal,

22:51.070 --> 22:52.200
buy a roast chicken,

22:53.460 --> 22:54.330
and think you've won me over?

22:54.330 --> 22:55.930
It's not just roast chicken.

22:59.380 --> 23:00.440
There's also this.

23:01.530 --> 23:02.510
You know me.

23:03.250 --> 23:04.510
I speak before I think.

23:05.900 --> 23:07.160
Words go in my ears,

23:07.160 --> 23:08.820
and I don't digest them first.

23:09.090 --> 23:10.180
But the most important thing

23:10.180 --> 23:11.570
is... is that I broke the rules.

23:11.570 --> 23:13.030
You said I wasn't allowed to
touch anything,

23:13.030 --> 23:14.070
but I... I still touched

23:14.070 --> 23:15.610
your most important things.

23:15.610 --> 23:16.110
Your

23:16.460 --> 23:17.390
creative ideas,

23:17.530 --> 23:18.220
your words,

23:18.790 --> 23:19.990
and your characters.

23:23.030 --> 23:23.880
Take this.

23:24.940 --> 23:26.200
In the future, if anyone here

23:26.200 --> 23:27.510
doesn't follow the rules,

23:27.510 --> 23:29.310
you can beat them without worry.

23:48.420 --> 23:48.950
How is it?

23:49.830 --> 23:50.430
Is it okay?

23:51.480 --> 23:52.900
To call it authentic

23:53.680 --> 23:55.400
would be flattery.

23:56.350 --> 23:57.810
This Sichuan dish of yours

23:58.050 --> 23:59.510
has the form

24:00.790 --> 24:03.550
but lacks the spirit of Sichuan cuisine.

24:04.310 --> 24:05.040
Understood.

24:05.570 --> 24:07.850
I'll strive for both form
and spirit next time.

24:07.850 --> 24:08.720
You kid.

24:09.920 --> 24:12.030
You're so scheming.

24:13.480 --> 24:14.510
Don't say that.

24:16.030 --> 24:17.000
If you eat well,

24:17.290 --> 24:18.620
you'll be in a good mood.

24:18.920 --> 24:20.250
If you're in a good mood,

24:20.440 --> 24:22.140
inspiration will flow like a spring.

24:22.140 --> 24:23.030
Then won't your writing

24:23.030 --> 24:24.290
get better and better?

24:31.270 --> 24:32.800
This dog-beating stick...

24:34.070 --> 24:35.070
feels handy.

24:35.610 --> 24:37.090
It's just a stick.

24:37.200 --> 24:38.720
It's not a dog-beating stick.

24:38.720 --> 24:39.780
I don't hit people.

24:40.480 --> 24:41.610
I only beat dogs.

24:42.750 --> 24:43.850
The logic at this point

24:43.850 --> 24:44.940
has to be written like this.

24:44.940 --> 24:45.980
Say that again.

24:46.240 --> 24:47.570
It has to be written like this

24:47.570 --> 24:48.300
at this part.

24:48.420 --> 24:48.880
Okay.

24:49.180 --> 24:50.840
Shut the door and beat the dog!

24:51.590 --> 24:52.320
Beat the dog.

24:52.530 --> 24:53.530
I'll beat the dog.

24:53.660 --> 24:55.720
-Beat me... You can't catch me!
-I will.

24:55.720 --> 24:56.180
I'll hit you.

24:56.180 --> 24:56.680
Come on.

24:57.180 --> 24:58.180
I'll beat the dog.

24:59.440 --> 25:00.040
Come here.

25:00.160 --> 25:00.960
Get over here.

25:01.420 --> 25:02.020
Come here.

25:02.350 --> 25:02.950
Come here.

25:03.090 --> 25:04.090
Don't be angry.

25:04.240 --> 25:05.000
Give it to me.

25:05.000 --> 25:05.700
I'll let you hit me.

25:05.700 --> 25:06.790
-Give it to me!
-I'll let you hit me.

25:06.790 --> 25:07.400
Give it to me!

25:07.400 --> 25:08.030
I'll let you hit me.

25:08.030 --> 25:09.160
Hit me. Go on.

25:09.200 --> 25:10.070
Master, hit me.

25:11.220 --> 25:12.880
Master, hit me.

25:15.550 --> 25:16.010
Okay.

25:16.940 --> 25:17.740
Keep writing.

25:18.660 --> 25:19.460
Keep writing.

26:00.330 --> 26:00.990
Mrs. Zheng,

26:01.480 --> 26:02.550
from now on,

26:02.550 --> 26:03.530
I'll come a bit early before class.

26:03.530 --> 26:04.330
If you need help

26:04.330 --> 26:05.250
with anything,

26:05.400 --> 26:06.090
just tell me.

26:06.090 --> 26:06.890
I can do it all.

26:07.330 --> 26:08.790
There's not much to help with.

26:08.790 --> 26:10.270
Just the usual chores.

26:10.380 --> 26:11.740
I can handle it myself.

26:14.220 --> 26:15.550
But coming early is fine.

26:15.550 --> 26:17.250
You can join us

26:17.980 --> 26:18.580
for a meal.

26:24.220 --> 26:25.460
Mrs. Zheng,

26:25.500 --> 26:27.560
your outfit looks really nice today.

26:29.200 --> 26:31.060
I've been wearing this for years.

26:33.250 --> 26:34.480
My mom kept telling me

26:34.480 --> 26:35.380
to ask you

26:35.610 --> 26:36.610
what kind of clothes

26:36.610 --> 26:37.660
and styles

26:37.680 --> 26:38.530
you like.

26:39.500 --> 26:41.030
We got a new batch

26:41.070 --> 26:42.350
of beautiful fabric recently.

26:42.350 --> 26:44.330
She wants to make a few outfits for you.

26:44.330 --> 26:46.250
Tell your mom not to go to any trouble.

26:46.250 --> 26:47.980
I just wear whatever,

26:48.240 --> 26:49.700
and I don't like going out.

26:59.030 --> 27:00.460
Does your mom make

27:01.010 --> 27:02.410
all the clothes you wear?

27:04.440 --> 27:06.510
I love reading fashion magazines.

27:06.720 --> 27:07.440
If I see

27:07.460 --> 27:08.180
a style I like,

27:08.180 --> 27:08.770
I write it down

27:08.770 --> 27:10.030
and have my mom make it.

27:11.700 --> 27:12.300
I actually

27:13.090 --> 27:13.700
brought something

27:13.700 --> 27:14.550
with me today.

27:27.000 --> 27:28.000
Look, Mrs. Zheng.

27:28.310 --> 27:29.460
My mom just made it.

27:29.770 --> 27:31.550
I estimated your measurements.

27:31.550 --> 27:32.980
See if it fits.

27:33.910 --> 27:34.270
Oh...

27:36.000 --> 27:37.220
It's already made?

27:40.030 --> 27:40.400
Wow,

27:40.680 --> 27:42.030
your mom is amazing.

27:42.030 --> 27:43.090
This...

27:44.740 --> 27:47.200
This is so beautiful.

27:47.440 --> 27:48.900
Your mom is incredible.

27:49.050 --> 27:50.250
There's a skirt, too.

27:50.440 --> 27:51.400
If it doesn't fit,

27:51.400 --> 27:52.750
I'll take it back and alter it.

27:52.750 --> 27:53.950
It's a two-piece set?

27:55.720 --> 27:56.180
This...

27:56.510 --> 27:57.090
It's so colorful.

27:57.090 --> 27:58.350
Is it too flashy for me?

27:58.420 --> 27:59.610
Not at all.

27:59.750 --> 28:00.510
It suits you perfectly.

28:00.510 --> 28:01.240
It suits your elegance.

28:01.240 --> 28:02.090
It's very classy.

28:02.090 --> 28:02.980
Really?

28:03.590 --> 28:04.290
Do I...

28:05.050 --> 28:05.570
Does it

28:05.680 --> 28:06.480
look good?

28:06.480 --> 28:07.340
It looks great.

28:07.920 --> 28:09.180
Why don't you try it on?

28:10.480 --> 28:11.140
I'll try it.

28:18.980 --> 28:19.510
How is it?

28:19.680 --> 28:21.420
-Beautiful, Mrs. Zheng.
-Beautiful, right?

28:21.420 --> 28:22.150
It's lovely.

28:23.740 --> 28:25.000
How are the shoulders?

28:25.090 --> 28:26.180
If it doesn't fit, tell me,

28:26.180 --> 28:26.850
and I'll alter it.

28:26.850 --> 28:27.770
It fits perfectly.

28:27.770 --> 28:29.070
Look, these shoulder pads

28:29.070 --> 28:30.530
make my head look smaller.

28:31.200 --> 28:32.720
You know how to alter clothes too?

28:32.720 --> 28:33.450
A little bit.

28:34.000 --> 28:35.060
You're so skilled.

28:35.240 --> 28:36.350
I'm glad you like it.

28:36.350 --> 28:37.270
I love it.

28:39.270 --> 28:39.670
Who...

28:40.550 --> 28:41.380
Who is this?

28:41.640 --> 28:42.640
It's Mrs. Zheng.

28:43.500 --> 28:43.920
No.

28:44.460 --> 28:45.550
It's a superstar.

28:46.050 --> 28:46.780
A superstar!

28:46.940 --> 28:48.030
You're never serious.

28:48.030 --> 28:48.960
It looks so good.

28:49.160 --> 28:51.020
Are these new clothes you bought?

28:51.550 --> 28:53.140
Zhuang Zhuang's mother made this for me.

28:53.140 --> 28:54.940
Zhuang Zhuang's mother made it?

28:55.050 --> 28:55.720
Zhuang Zhuang,

28:55.720 --> 28:57.200
ask your mother to make one for me too.

28:57.200 --> 28:57.660
Sure.

28:57.750 --> 28:58.690
So that I can

28:58.830 --> 29:00.490
be worthy of my wife.

29:00.610 --> 29:01.290
No problem.

29:02.700 --> 29:05.570
I've seen thousands of beautiful girls,

29:05.790 --> 29:09.780
but only you are the loveliest.

29:09.960 --> 29:11.240
So beautiful.

29:11.480 --> 29:12.900
Don't I look good usually?

29:12.900 --> 29:14.410
You always look great.

29:14.500 --> 29:16.700
But today you are especially stunning.

29:19.130 --> 29:20.550
[Beijing Station]

29:20.630 --> 29:21.700
[Tickets]

29:23.250 --> 29:23.880
Hello.

29:24.010 --> 29:25.330
One ticket to Guangzhou, please.

29:25.330 --> 29:26.120
223 yuan.

29:27.180 --> 29:30.450
[Ticket Hall]

29:27.500 --> 29:27.850
Hello.

29:27.850 --> 29:29.380
I want a ticket to Nanchang.

29:29.680 --> 29:30.530
Nanchang.

29:32.750 --> 29:33.200
Hello.

29:33.440 --> 29:33.770
Hello.

29:33.770 --> 29:35.270
Ten seated tickets for Train 134

29:35.270 --> 29:36.730
from Beijing to Shanghai.

29:36.810 --> 29:38.070
Why do you need so many?

29:38.270 --> 29:39.460
My company is going on a business trip.

29:39.460 --> 29:40.500
They asked me to buy tickets.

29:40.500 --> 29:41.360
Which company?

29:41.500 --> 29:42.560
Wait a moment.

29:46.480 --> 29:48.340
Here's the introduction letter.

29:56.680 --> 29:57.530
1,170 yuan.

29:58.140 --> 29:58.470
Okay.

30:02.930 --> 30:05.680
[Ticket Hall]

30:14.460 --> 30:15.220
-Ten tickets.
-Thank you.

30:15.220 --> 30:16.150
You're welcome.

30:17.460 --> 30:20.080
[Ticket Office]

30:20.240 --> 30:20.900
Kid.

30:21.400 --> 30:22.110
Where's the money

30:22.110 --> 30:22.880
I told you to bring last week?

30:22.880 --> 30:24.940
-Collecting rangehoods!
-Where’s the money?

30:24.940 --> 30:25.980
Is it in your pocket?

30:25.980 --> 30:27.200
Where did you put the money?

30:27.200 --> 30:28.200
Not in the pocket.

30:28.610 --> 30:29.480
Don't meddle.

30:32.920 --> 30:33.980
Where's the money?

30:34.180 --> 30:35.240
The money you made.

30:35.700 --> 30:36.100
Money.

30:36.960 --> 30:38.420
Why are you bullying a disabled person?

30:38.420 --> 30:39.790
Are you two even human?

30:39.920 --> 30:41.180
None of your business.

30:43.140 --> 30:44.330
I'll kill you!

30:44.380 --> 30:45.400
He's crazy. Run.

30:45.480 --> 30:46.090
He's crazy.

30:46.090 --> 30:47.500
I'll kill you!

30:47.680 --> 30:48.030
I...

30:58.380 --> 30:59.380
Are you okay, kid?

31:02.000 --> 31:02.600
Come here.

31:08.000 --> 31:09.000
Are you all right?

31:10.610 --> 31:12.500
Where do you live?

31:15.720 --> 31:17.400
I can hear you.

31:17.640 --> 31:19.010
You can hear a little?

31:24.420 --> 31:26.030
What is this?

31:28.200 --> 31:29.090
A hearing aid?

31:30.030 --> 31:31.880
Artificial cochlear.

31:33.830 --> 31:34.850
Artificial what?

31:46.830 --> 31:49.390
[Artificial cochlear]

31:47.140 --> 31:49.510
Cochlear.

31:50.420 --> 31:51.830
Artificial cochlear?

31:55.830 --> 31:57.790
[Artificial cochlear. Put it in]

31:59.760 --> 32:01.660
[And I can hear.]

32:03.270 --> 32:03.980
Really?

32:05.460 --> 32:06.140
How did you

32:06.680 --> 32:07.460
go deaf?

32:10.840 --> 32:12.920
[I had a fever when I was young]

32:14.730 --> 32:16.250
[I had a fever when I was young
and then I went deaf.]

32:18.110 --> 32:20.340
[I couldn't talk after that.]

32:21.140 --> 32:23.290
You go deaf first, then mute, too?

32:24.980 --> 32:27.200
Where did you get this done?

32:29.830 --> 32:31.550
[In Beijing.]

32:33.610 --> 32:34.200
Child,

32:34.960 --> 32:37.170
write down everything you know

32:37.440 --> 32:39.090
for me.

32:39.220 --> 32:41.450
Which hospital? Which specialist?

32:48.910 --> 32:49.550
[Beijing Association Hospital
ENT Department]

32:49.580 --> 32:50.610
[Attending Physician Zhang Jicong]

32:52.140 --> 32:52.660
Child,

32:53.330 --> 32:55.440
how much did this cost?

32:57.770 --> 32:59.170
For the first time alone,

32:59.940 --> 33:01.070
it was 80,000 yuan?

33:09.010 --> 33:11.480
Like a thunderclap,

33:12.290 --> 33:15.010
I, a loyal subject defending the country,

33:15.550 --> 33:18.110
step out of Tianbo Mansion.

33:18.920 --> 33:23.330
A golden crown weighs upon my temples.

33:24.030 --> 33:26.330
The iron armor of old,

33:26.350 --> 33:28.240
I put on my body once more.

33:29.230 --> 33:31.330
[Seasons Change Hostel]

33:58.550 --> 34:02.610
Rows of green mountains

34:02.750 --> 34:06.160
are closely connected.

34:08.320 --> 34:10.960
Closely...

34:11.000 --> 34:12.420
-Come, Zhuang Zhuang.
-This nose.

34:12.420 --> 34:13.480
Come, take a break.

34:14.860 --> 34:16.550
We just started. We're not tired.

34:16.550 --> 34:17.380
Who's not tired?

34:17.380 --> 34:18.840
Even if you aren't, she is.

34:18.860 --> 34:20.520
Come over and have some fruit.

34:21.400 --> 34:21.929
Sit down.

34:23.840 --> 34:24.380
Sit.

34:25.760 --> 34:27.020
Thank you, Mrs. Zheng.

34:27.880 --> 34:28.280
Here.

34:28.820 --> 34:29.820
Have a tangerine.

34:32.550 --> 34:33.409
Zhuang Zhuang,

34:33.960 --> 34:34.710
why have you booked

34:34.710 --> 34:36.110
so few classes recently?

34:36.960 --> 34:37.460
I...

34:38.530 --> 34:40.130
Regarding the tuition fees,

34:40.170 --> 34:41.170
we let you owe us,

34:41.550 --> 34:42.750
yet you pull this on us

34:42.780 --> 34:44.440
and just stop coming to class.

34:45.510 --> 34:46.360
Zhuang Zhuang,

34:46.360 --> 34:48.090
I think you looking for odd jobs

34:48.280 --> 34:49.570
everywhere in Beijing

34:49.860 --> 34:51.070
isn't a long-term solution.

34:51.070 --> 34:52.270
It's not safe either.

34:55.489 --> 34:58.460
[Yue Ru]

34:56.460 --> 34:58.150
This is a designer that a friend of mine

34:58.150 --> 34:59.570
worked with before.

34:59.820 --> 35:01.430
He said this designer

35:01.350 --> 35:01.930
[Yue Ru]

35:01.450 --> 35:02.640
is very creative.

35:02.110 --> 35:03.290
[Ruhua Costume Company]

35:03.760 --> 35:05.530
Apparently, he's designed clothes

35:05.530 --> 35:06.230
for many stars

35:06.230 --> 35:07.340
and singers.

35:08.110 --> 35:09.090
I see that the things

35:09.090 --> 35:10.010
this company designs

35:10.010 --> 35:11.000
are all very trendy.

35:11.000 --> 35:12.230
It just so happens that this designer

35:12.230 --> 35:13.360
needs an assistant,

35:13.400 --> 35:13.900
so I recommended you

35:13.900 --> 35:14.630
to him.

35:16.090 --> 35:17.550
Recommended for me to work there?

35:17.550 --> 35:18.190
Yes.

35:19.840 --> 35:20.690
I was thinking

35:20.760 --> 35:21.880
you could give it a try

35:21.880 --> 35:22.780
if you need it.

35:23.050 --> 35:24.250
If it's not suitable,

35:24.590 --> 35:25.170
I won't force you.

35:25.170 --> 35:25.730
I need it.

35:27.030 --> 35:27.960
I really need it.

35:30.260 --> 35:30.800
Once you have

35:30.800 --> 35:31.880
a stable income,

35:31.940 --> 35:33.280
your family will be at ease.

35:33.280 --> 35:34.510
You don't need to worry

35:34.510 --> 35:36.130
about the tuition fees either.

35:36.130 --> 35:37.590
Just attend your classes,

35:38.190 --> 35:39.230
and don't let down

35:39.260 --> 35:41.120
Mr. Zheng's expectations of you.

35:41.510 --> 35:42.580
Right, Mr. Zheng?

35:44.170 --> 35:44.880
Mrs. Zheng,

35:45.280 --> 35:46.880
you're very understanding.

35:49.030 --> 35:50.290
Thank you, Mrs. Zheng.

35:52.260 --> 35:54.130
Why are you crying?

35:55.530 --> 35:56.210
From now on,

35:57.110 --> 35:58.730
work hard and sing well.

36:00.300 --> 36:01.360
Achieving success

36:02.010 --> 36:03.540
is the best repayment to us.

36:04.260 --> 36:04.710
I will.

36:08.710 --> 36:10.050
Mom. Mom.

36:10.900 --> 36:12.940
Dad sent a letter.

36:23.700 --> 36:26.260
[Guo Zongbao's Letter]

36:35.550 --> 36:35.900
Mom,

36:36.010 --> 36:37.130
why are you crying?

36:38.170 --> 36:39.500
What are you crying for?

36:50.670 --> 36:51.260
Mom.

36:51.940 --> 36:53.340
Dad said,

36:53.550 --> 36:54.280
next year,

36:54.630 --> 36:55.620
he'll take you

36:56.070 --> 36:57.630
to Beijing

36:57.980 --> 36:59.050
for surgery.

36:59.820 --> 37:03.380
He'll find the best experts
in the country.

37:05.590 --> 37:06.110
Mom,

37:07.400 --> 37:09.770
you'll be able to speak soon.

37:12.000 --> 37:13.710
You should be happy.

37:14.010 --> 37:17.530
I am happy. Happy.

37:23.530 --> 37:24.110
Mom.

37:24.900 --> 37:26.760
Dad also said

37:27.300 --> 37:28.900
he's making good money

37:29.480 --> 37:32.030
in Beijing.

37:32.960 --> 37:33.510
I...

37:33.570 --> 37:35.710
sometimes can't sleep at night.

37:36.610 --> 37:39.400
I think about how big Beijing is.

37:39.940 --> 37:41.920
Dad is so capable.

37:42.230 --> 37:44.160
He can act in Beijing.

37:44.780 --> 37:46.590
When I grow up,

37:47.300 --> 37:49.610
I'll join Dad

37:50.070 --> 37:52.000
to act in Beijing.

37:58.090 --> 38:00.050
Do you miss Dad?

38:11.090 --> 38:11.800
Mom.

38:12.610 --> 38:14.190
The other day at school,

38:14.960 --> 38:16.110
we had a show.

38:16.880 --> 38:19.510
I performed a skit.

38:20.510 --> 38:21.400
The principal

38:21.760 --> 38:23.050
said it was great.

38:24.840 --> 38:26.610
I told the principal

38:27.440 --> 38:30.150
it runs in the family.

38:52.260 --> 38:52.730
Thanks.

39:00.900 --> 39:03.360
[Ticket Office]

39:01.820 --> 39:02.150
Watch it.

39:02.150 --> 39:02.940
Sorry.

39:03.050 --> 39:04.250
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

39:04.280 --> 39:05.090
No need. I'll do it myself.

39:05.090 --> 39:05.760
No problem.

39:07.770 --> 39:09.810
[Beijing to Nanjing]

39:08.010 --> 39:08.790
Seriously.

39:11.820 --> 39:13.180
Are your tickets fake?

39:15.880 --> 39:17.410
I've seen you here for days.

39:18.320 --> 39:19.250
I'm warning you.

39:19.590 --> 39:20.720
We're all scalpers.

39:21.030 --> 39:22.000
Don't meddle in my business.

39:22.000 --> 39:23.420
I'm buying for my company.

39:23.420 --> 39:23.820
You...

39:25.320 --> 39:26.820
So nosy. What bad luck.

39:27.010 --> 39:27.540
Get lost.

39:29.360 --> 39:30.590
Attention, everyone.

39:30.590 --> 39:31.860
Someone is selling fake tickets here!

39:31.570 --> 39:35.210
[Ticket Office]

39:35.240 --> 39:40.210
[Ticket Hall]

39:40.300 --> 39:41.940
[Enter the station with your ticket]
[Security Check]

39:42.190 --> 39:43.520
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

39:43.610 --> 39:44.470
Officer.

39:44.780 --> 39:45.790
I saw a man

39:45.980 --> 39:46.880
wearing a white shirt,

39:46.880 --> 39:48.030
carrying a black shoulder bag,

39:48.030 --> 39:49.730
and holding a bunch of tickets.

39:49.730 --> 39:51.420
He was about this tall.

39:51.840 --> 39:53.240
I suspect he's a scalper.

39:53.650 --> 39:54.580
He went that way.

39:54.820 --> 39:56.880
Okay. Thank you for the information.

40:05.130 --> 40:05.930
Need tickets?

40:07.070 --> 40:07.560
No.

40:07.880 --> 40:08.500
Got them already, right?

40:08.500 --> 40:08.860
Yes.

40:08.900 --> 40:09.300
Okay.

40:10.730 --> 40:11.490
Ladies.

40:12.030 --> 40:13.440
Where are you going? Need tickets?

40:13.440 --> 40:14.050
No, no, no.

40:14.050 --> 40:15.510
We bought them ourselves.

40:18.880 --> 40:19.330
Buddy.

40:19.670 --> 40:20.800
Where are you going?

40:20.860 --> 40:21.660
Need tickets?

40:22.280 --> 40:23.280
Got them already?

40:23.800 --> 40:24.190
Mom.

40:24.880 --> 40:25.800
There's only one train

40:25.800 --> 40:26.810
to Jiangxi.

40:28.650 --> 40:29.170
Did you get tickets?

40:29.170 --> 40:30.170
Let me check here.

40:31.610 --> 40:33.270
There's nothing here either.

40:33.440 --> 40:33.900
This...

40:34.920 --> 40:35.340
Ma'am,

40:36.210 --> 40:37.410
where are you headed?

40:37.650 --> 40:38.400
Nanchang.

40:38.630 --> 40:39.280
I have tickets.

40:39.280 --> 40:40.630
I have tickets to everywhere.

40:40.630 --> 40:42.030
-Do you want it?
-Really?

40:42.190 --> 40:43.080
Let me see.

40:43.580 --> 40:45.370
[Beijing to Nanjing]

40:44.000 --> 40:45.400
Look. The ticket is fine.

40:46.510 --> 40:47.770
All right. Give me two.

40:48.010 --> 40:48.630
How much?

40:48.800 --> 40:49.600
200 yuan each.

40:50.230 --> 40:51.300
200?

40:51.780 --> 40:52.380
At the ticket window,

40:52.380 --> 40:53.940
it's only 80-something.

40:54.670 --> 40:55.550
Keep it down.

40:55.730 --> 40:56.340
If you can't afford it,

40:56.340 --> 40:57.280
go to the window.

40:58.000 --> 40:59.500
No, look.

40:59.670 --> 41:01.230
My father-in-law is sick.

41:01.270 --> 41:02.770
I have to go back today.

41:02.920 --> 41:03.780
They said at the window

41:03.780 --> 41:05.210
that there are no tickets left.

41:05.210 --> 41:06.190
People come here to buy tickets

41:06.190 --> 41:07.860
for urgent matters.

41:07.900 --> 41:09.030
I can't sell to you without the money.

41:09.030 --> 41:09.760
No, no, sir.

41:09.760 --> 41:10.230
No, no.

41:10.320 --> 41:10.920
Let's talk this over.

41:10.920 --> 41:11.980
What are you doing?

41:12.130 --> 41:13.300
Aren't these tickets

41:13.300 --> 41:14.700
bought for your company?

41:15.420 --> 41:16.350
You bought them?

41:16.460 --> 41:17.000
Come on, give me the tickets.

41:17.000 --> 41:18.510
No, explain it clearly first.

41:18.510 --> 41:19.310
Young man,

41:19.480 --> 41:20.030
do you have

41:20.030 --> 41:21.110
tickets to Nanchang?

41:21.110 --> 41:21.780
No.

41:21.780 --> 41:22.300
Yes,

41:22.340 --> 41:23.780
I have tickets to Nanchang.

41:23.780 --> 41:24.320
Great.

41:24.400 --> 41:25.650
Please sell me two.

41:26.280 --> 41:28.030
My father-in-law is sick.

41:28.320 --> 41:29.880
They said there are no tickets left
at the counter.

41:29.880 --> 41:30.960
We're not selling anything. We can't.

41:30.960 --> 41:31.840
These are for our company.

41:31.840 --> 41:32.980
How much did he say

41:32.980 --> 41:34.070
a ticket costs?

41:35.230 --> 41:35.760
200.

41:38.840 --> 41:39.730
How many do you need?

41:39.730 --> 41:41.260
I'll sell them to you at face value.

41:41.260 --> 41:42.050
I need two.

41:46.570 --> 41:47.770
Mom, take the ticket.

41:48.710 --> 41:49.410
Young man,

41:49.550 --> 41:51.440
I won't let you do this for nothing.

41:51.440 --> 41:52.000
180.

41:52.630 --> 41:53.840
No need. 170 is fine.

41:54.500 --> 41:55.390
Thank you.

41:55.590 --> 41:56.560
Mom, let's go.

41:56.690 --> 41:57.280
Hurry up and go.

41:57.280 --> 41:58.500
You're such a rip-off!

41:58.500 --> 41:59.420
Hurry. Let's go, Mom.

41:59.420 --> 42:00.880
We're running out of time.

42:03.480 --> 42:04.120
What?

42:05.260 --> 42:06.860
Done being a Good Samaritan?

42:07.570 --> 42:08.990
Are you out of your mind?

42:09.300 --> 42:10.480
I brought you here to make money.

42:10.480 --> 42:11.570
Why are you fighting me on this?

42:11.570 --> 42:13.280
Does this have anything to do with money?

42:13.280 --> 42:14.280
Why did you lie to me?

42:14.280 --> 42:14.860
Didn't you say

42:14.860 --> 42:16.230
they were tickets for the company?

42:16.230 --> 42:17.630
This is called scalping.

42:17.860 --> 42:19.460
Fine, fine. You're the boss.

42:19.630 --> 42:20.690
Can we keep it down?

42:21.010 --> 42:21.660
I give up.

42:22.210 --> 42:22.920
Give me the tickets.

42:22.920 --> 42:23.280
No.

42:23.880 --> 42:24.530
I paid for them.

42:24.530 --> 42:26.130
Why won't you give them to me?

42:26.760 --> 42:27.800
Then I'll give you the money.

42:27.800 --> 42:28.840
I don't want money. I want the tickets.

42:28.840 --> 42:29.860
-Come on, give me the tickets.
-Stop pulling.

42:29.860 --> 42:30.780
I'm going to scream.

42:30.780 --> 42:31.640
I'm screaming.

42:33.200 --> 42:34.260
Okay, okay. Fine.

42:34.510 --> 42:36.240
Give me the money. Hand it over.

42:37.460 --> 42:37.980
I don't get it.

42:37.980 --> 42:39.240
What are you thinking?

42:39.300 --> 42:40.170
You make so little money,

42:40.170 --> 42:41.340
and it hasn't even warmed your pocket.

42:41.340 --> 42:42.340
What's the point?

42:42.920 --> 42:44.420
No wonder you're an artist.

42:44.420 --> 42:45.780
What's wrong with doing art?

42:45.780 --> 42:47.340
I'd rather starve to death
than take your money!

42:47.340 --> 42:48.800
Shut your mouth. Give me the money.

42:48.800 --> 42:50.010
Don't move, both of you.

42:50.010 --> 42:51.570
Please cooperate with our investigation.

42:51.570 --> 42:52.550
He... He is reselling illegally.

42:52.550 --> 42:53.220
Quiet!

42:53.460 --> 42:54.940
We'll know once the investigation is done.
